The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Hurst, Broad appointed match referees 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Hurst, Broad appointed match referees 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) on Wednesday appointed Allan Hurst and Chris Broad as match referees for the ensuing India-Sri Lanka Test and one-day International series respectively.         
	According to an ICC release, Englands Mark Benson and the West Indian Billy Doctrove will officiate the opening Test at the Sinhalese Sports Club in Colombo from July 23-27.         
	Doctrove will be accompanied by South African Rudi Koertzen for the second Test in Galle starting from July 31 while Benson and Koertzen will stand in the third and final Test at Colombos Premadasa Stadium scheduled from August 8.         
	Meanwhile, the entire ODI series will be officiated by Doctrove and a local umpire.         
	The Test series will also witness the trial of the umpire decision review system with Koertzen as the TV umpire in the first Test while Benson and Doctrove will fill the role in the second and third Tests, respectively. The review system trial will not be applicable to the following ODI series.         
	OFFICIALS FOR TEST SERIES         
	Match Referee  Alan Hurst         
	First Test: July 23-27  Sri Lanka v India, SSC, Colombo  Mark Benson amp; Billy Doctrove; TV Umpire  Rudi Koertzen         
	Second Test: July 31-August 4  Sri Lanka v India, Galle  Billy Doctrove amp; Rudi Koertzen; TV Umpire  Mark Benson         
	Third Test: August 8-12  Sri Lanka v India, R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo  Rudi Koertzen amp; Mark Benson; TV Umpire  Billy Doctrove               
	OFFICIALS FOR ODI series         
	Match Referee  Chris Broad         
	First ODI: August 18  Sri Lanka v India, Dambulla  Billy Doctrove and local appointment         
	Second ODI: August 20  Sri Lanka v India, Dambulla  Billy Doctrove and local appointment         
	Third ODI: August 24  Sri Lanka v India, R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo  Billy Doctrove and local appointment         
	Fourth ODI: August 26  Sri Lanka v India, R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo  Billy Doctrove and local appointment         
	Fifth ODI: August 29  Sri Lanka v India, R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo  Billy Doctrove and local appointment.                                                                                                                          
